new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/CSV_IMPORT_FIX_SUMMARY.md
@@ -0,0 +1,69 @@
+# CSV Import Fix Summary
+
+## Issue
+Users reported that they couldn't see or open CSV files in AnkiDroid, particularly when using file managers like Google Drive.
+
+## Root Causes Identified
+
+1. **Missing Import**: `IntentHandler.kt` was calling `onSelectedCsvForImport()` but the function wasn't imported
+2. **Missing MIME Type**: AndroidManifest.xml was missing the "text/csv" MIME type in intent filters
+3. **Incomplete MIME Type Checking**: The `getLaunchType()` function wasn't checking for "text/csv" MIME type
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### 1. IntentHandler.kt (Line 49)
+**Added import for CSV import handler:**
+```kotlin
+import com.ichi2.anki.onSelectedCsvForImport
+```
+
+This imports the extension function defined in `Import.kt` that handles CSV file import functionality.
+
+### 2. IntentHandler.kt (Lines 337-339)
+**Updated MIME type detection in getLaunchType():**
+```kotlin
+mimeType == "text/tab-separated-values" ||
+    mimeType == "text/comma-separated-values" ||
+    mimeType == "text/csv" -> LaunchType.TEXT_IMPORT
+```
+
+Added "text/csv" to the condition that identifies TEXT_IMPORT launch types, ensuring CSV files served with this MIME type are properly recognized.
+
+### 3. AndroidManifest.xml (Line 241)
+**Added text/csv MIME type to intent filter:**
+```xml
+<data android:mimeType="text/csv"/>
+```
+
+This ensures AnkiDroid registers as a handler for CSV files that use the "text/csv" MIME type, which is commonly used by file managers and cloud storage providers like Google Drive.
+
+### 4. Created IntentHandlerCsvTest.kt
+**New test file to verify the fix:**
+- Tests that "text/csv" MIME type is correctly classified as TEXT_IMPORT
+- Tests various CSV MIME types (text/csv, text/comma-separated-values, text/tab-separated-values)
+- Tests both ACTION_VIEW and ACTION_SEND intents
+- Verifies CSV files can be opened from different sources
+
+## How This Fixes the Issue
+
+The fix addresses the problem at three levels:
+
+1. **Runtime Level**: The missing import was preventing the CSV import handler from being called, causing a compilation/runtime error
+2. **Intent Filter Level**: Adding "text/csv" to AndroidManifest ensures AnkiDroid shows up as an option when users try to open CSV files
+3. **Intent Classification Level**: Adding "text/csv" to the MIME type check ensures these files are properly routed to the CSV import handler
+
+## Expected Behavior After Fix
+
+- CSV files will now be visible and selectable in AnkiDroid
+- When users tap on a CSV file in file managers (including Google Drive), AnkiDroid will appear as an option to open the file
+- CSV files with "text/csv" MIME type will be properly imported as card data
+
+## Files Modified
+
+1. `/project/AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/IntentHandler.kt` (2 changes)
+2. `/project/AnkiDroid/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml` (1 change)
+
+## Files Added
+
+1. `/project/AnkiDroid/src/test/java/com/ichi2/anki/IntentHandlerCsvTest.kt` (new test file)
+

