+# CSV Import Fix - Verification Trace
+
+## User Workflow - Before Fix
+
+1. User has CSV file in Google Drive
+2. User taps on CSV file to open it
+3. Google Drive sends Intent with:
+   - Action: VIEW or SEND
+   - MIME type: "text/csv"
+4. **❌ FAIL**: AnkiDroid not in the list of apps that can open the file
+   - Reason: AndroidManifest.xml missing "text/csv" in intent filters
+
+## User Workflow - After Fix (Scenario 1)
+
+1. User has CSV file in Google Drive
+2. User taps on CSV file to open it
+3. Google Drive sends Intent with:
+   - Action: VIEW or SEND
+   - MIME type: "text/csv"
+4. **✅ SUCCESS**: AnkiDroid appears in the list of apps
+   - Fix: Added `<data android:mimeType="text/csv"/>` to AndroidManifest.xml
+5. User selects AnkiDroid
+6. **✅ SUCCESS**: Intent received by IntentHandler.onCreate()
+7. **✅ SUCCESS**: getLaunchType() checks MIME type "text/csv" and returns LaunchType.TEXT_IMPORT
+   - Fix: Added `mimeType == "text/csv"` to the condition
+8. **✅ SUCCESS**: onSelectedCsvForImport(fileIntent) is called
+   - Fix: Added `import com.ichi2.anki.onSelectedCsvForImport`
+9. **✅ SUCCESS**: CSV file is imported
+
+## User Workflow - After Fix (Scenario 2: Within App)
+
+1. User opens AnkiDroid
+2. User goes to import menu
+3. User selects "Import CSV"
+4. File picker opens with MIME types including "text/csv"
+   - Already supported in ImportFileSelectionFragment.kt
+5. User selects CSV file
+6. **✅ SUCCESS**: Same flow as Scenario 1, steps 6-9
+
+## Code Path Verification
+
+### IntentHandler.kt
+```kotlin
+override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
+    // ...
+    val launchType = getLaunchType(intent)  // Returns TEXT_IMPORT for "text/csv"
+    
+    when (launchType) {
+        LaunchType.TEXT_IMPORT ->
+            runIfStoragePermissions {
+                onSelectedCsvForImport(fileIntent)  // ✅ Imported function
+                finish()
+            }
+    }
+}
+```
+
+### getLaunchType() function
+```kotlin
+fun getLaunchType(intent: Intent): LaunchType {
+    val action = intent.action
+    return if (action == Intent.ACTION_SEND || Intent.ACTION_VIEW == action && isValidViewIntent(intent)) {
+        val mimeType = intent.resolveMimeType()
+        when {
+            mimeType == "text/tab-separated-values" ||
+                mimeType == "text/comma-separated-values" ||
+                mimeType == "text/csv" -> LaunchType.TEXT_IMPORT  // ✅ Added "text/csv"
+            else -> LaunchType.FILE_IMPORT
+        }
+    }
+    // ...
+}
+```
+
+### AndroidManifest.xml Intent Filter
+```xml
+<intent-filter>
+    <action android:name="android.intent.action.VIEW" />
+    <category android:name="android.intent.category.DEFAULT" />
+    <data android:mimeType="text/tab-separated-values"/>
+    <data android:mimeType="text/comma-separated-values"/>
+    <data android:mimeType="text/csv"/>  <!-- ✅ Added -->
+</intent-filter>
+```
+
+## Test Coverage
+
+### IntentHandlerCsvTest.kt
+- ✅ Tests "text/csv" MIME type with ACTION_VIEW
+- ✅ Tests "text/csv" MIME type with ACTION_SEND
+- ✅ Tests CSV files with various MIME types
+- ✅ Tests file paths with .csv extension
+
+## Verification Result
+
+**All three issues are fixed:**
+1. ✅ Import statement added
+2. ✅ MIME type added to manifest
+3. ✅ MIME type check added to getLaunchType()
+
+**Expected outcome:**
+- Users can now see CSV files as importable in AnkiDroid
+- CSV files from Google Drive and other sources will work
+- Existing CSV import functionality (TSV, comma-separated) remains intact
+
